content: On perf.rust-lang.org the graph for await-call-tree-debug shows a incremental-full regression from commit 23aef90b4e with 236,888,240 instructions to commit 2e7eb85b1d with 250,215,330 instructions. But when I open a comparison page by clicking on either of those commits, the low-end measurment doesn't match and is 250,274,004 instead.
Similarly, if I open largest regression on externs-check graph, the comparison page shows a large improvement ...
Thanks for noticing! I'll try to take a look at this, but it would be great to file an issue so it doesn't get lost. @tm could you do that?
Everything seems to be working fine right now. Not sure if you already had a time to fix it, but in any case I will open an issue if I encounter the problem once again. Thanks.
Hm, I did not change anything, so not sure what caused it then.
